        "timestamp": "2017-09-19 21:30:12.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nOk, in that case, can you guys help set this up?  I don't really know what system-scripts, resource type, system_matrix, etc. mean that you were referring to.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "3c1e26b7bae968c27d86a46176e20ade0ff566a3",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1,
          "name": "Andrew Grimberg",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "agrimberg@linuxfoundation.org",
          "username": "agrimberg"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-09-19 21:34:52.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Ok, in that case, can you guys help set this up?  I don't really\n > know what system-scripts, resource type, system_matrix, etc. mean\n > that you were referring to.\n\njenkins-scripts == the jenkins-scripts directory in this repository. If you open the system_type.sh script you'll see an for loop using an IFS of ',' that's the system matrix that was being referred to.\n\nThe docker bits will need to be put into a docker.sh file which will be a new file.\n\nsystem_type.sh is a switching mechanism for determining a portion of a hostname that should map to a configuration script. This is how we map the provisioning / template to any specialized startup scripts and is why our minions all encode their packer template information into their name.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
